FastAPI -> python based web framework
scarlet -> build in top of starlet for the web parts
pydantic -> data part

React -> pjavascript library for building user interfaces

mongodb -> document oriented no sql database stores data in flexible json like documents ; meaning datastructes can be changed overtime

FastAPI ->
pip install "fastapi[standard]"
-> install

pip install "fastapi[all]"
from typing import union 

code ->
app = FastAPI()
✔️ Creates your FastAPI application
✔️ Used to define all API endpoints
✔️ Uvicorn runs this object

@app.get("/")
4 examples
@ → decorator symbol.
app → FastAPI application instance.
get → HTTP method for retrieval.
"/" → root URL path

/items/10
Returns:
{
  "item_id": 10,
  "q": null
}
/items/10?q=phone
Returns:
{
  "item_id": 10,
  "q": "phone"
}

the ? marks seperates the items value and q value ->
? : is how the urls work, it is standard format.
/items/30?q=20p
{
  "item_id": 30,
  "q": "20p"
}

(/path?query#fragment)

we run the server using uvicorn server -> pip install uvicorn
FastAPI is built on ASGI (Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface).
Uvicorn is an ASGI server.
Both are fully async → extremely fast.

-> uvicorn main:app --reload















